oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Western State Hospital cemetery
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of a group of men cleaning up the cemetery at Western State Hospital. A car and other buildings can be seen in the background. A typed note on the photo reads "Hospital Cemetery repair and Memorial Day 1958-1959." A handwritten note on the photo reads "One of Mrs. Levys' many projects to improve W.S. Hospt."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
